channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: The Swiss Debt Brake Is the Patek Philippe of Fiscal Rules
Top 5 moments from Trump's Fox News town hall in key battleground state: 'World War III territory'
item.description: Former President Donald Trump joined Fox News' Sean Hannity in Harrisburg, Pennsylvania, for a town hall event, where he fielded questions from voters.

item.title: Musk Offers to Help Trump Drain the Swamp
item.description: Telsa CEO Elon Musk doubled down on his promise to help dial back on the size and scope of government should former President Donald Trump win a second term.

item.title: Free Speech Is on the Ballot: Jonathan Turley Shreds Harris for Her Hostility to the 1st Amendment
Hunter Biden's criminal tax trial begins with jury selection in California
item.description: Jury selection in Hunter Biden’s criminal tax trial in California, stemming from special counsel David Weiss’ yearslong investigation into the first son, begins Thursday.

item.title: Tulsi Gabbard to Newsmax: Put on Terror Watchlist After Criticizing Harris
item.description: Former Rep. Tulsi Gabbard, D-Hawaii, who is working with former President Donald Trump's campaign, told Newsmax on Wednesday she was targeted by the Biden administration after criticizing Vice President Kamala Harris.

item.title: MSNBC Hosts Slack Off From 'Journalism' Duties During Fox News' Trump Town Hall, Repeating a Tired Smear
Trump to skip federal court hearing Thursday, plead not guilty to charges in Jack Smith's election case
item.description: Lawyers are expected to enter a not guilty plea on behalf of former President Trump in a federal court arraignment in Washington, D.C., Thursday.

item.title: Lewandowski to Newsmax: Voting for Trump Key to the Future
item.description: Trump campaign official Corey Lewandowski told Newsmax on Wednesday that Americans should vote for former President Donald Trump if they want economic recovery, national security, and the restoration of law and order across the country.

item.title: In Town Hall, Trump Calls Out Kamala's Embarrassing Sham of an Interview With CNN
Southern border crisis helped spur massive spike in crossings from Canada as well: expert
item.description: The spike in migrant crossings at the northern border have happened in part because resources have been diverted to help solve the crisis at the southern border.

item.title: No Surprise: Liz Cheney Voting for Harris
item.description: Former Wyoming Rep. Liz Cheney, a leading Republican critic of former President Donald Trump who was part of the committee overseeing impeachment hearings, told a crowd in North Carolina on Wednesday that she plans to vote for Vice President Kamala Harris this...

item.title: Trump Town Hall: Trump Says Kamala 'Wants to Be Politically Correct' in Dealing With Hamas, Global Terror
How Trump, or Kamala, could win, as all sides zero in on the debate
item.description: With next Tuesday's debate in pundits' crosshairs, few appear comfortable admitting that the presidential election, as it stands today, is about as evenly-matched as you can get.

item.title: Sen. Mullin to Newsmax: Soft-on-Crime Agenda Bad for America
item.description: The Harris-Walz platform is more about a political agenda than it is about America, Sen. Markwayne Mullin, R-Okla., told Newsmax Wednesday. In an appearance on "Prime News," the Oklahoma Republican said the same thing is true in cities and states across the country.
